 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uheihache.showPublicProfile?language=EN>heihache</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/1/01 12:24:30 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.iquest.net/~jynx25/me.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Im a noob to the Wizzy classs</span><hr size=1> At lvl 8, it depends where you are for hunting.  In Faydar, head over to Steamfont and kill stuff at the windmill.  If in FP, go to Nro and do jackals and Orc raiders, Qyenos head to outside Blackburrow, and if camped, head to the otherside (Everfrost) and do the ones in the tunnel there, if in Tox, hit the warrens.  <p><a href=#><img src=http://members.iquest.net/~jynx25/robe.jpg border=0></a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/1/01 1:32:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Im a noob to the Wizzy classs</span><hr size=1> Here is my 2CP<br>
<br>
Starting at 8th, go to the orc camps in EC and stay till you hit about 12. Make sure to turn in the belts. Learn to group here. You will learn about singles, and over pulls -- and how to manage both. if you need extra cash, sell the belts. When you hit about 12, go to the derv camps for 2 or 3 levels, then over to Croc hunting in Oasis. Keep grouping. You'll get PLENTY of time to solo later in life, but learing to group is a good thing. At 15, go to orc highway till 17, then head over to the Lake of Ill Omen. Stay put till 22. Resiste the urge to go to the giants. Get a good group, and stick with it. By this time, choose a good guild and get into it. They will be your source of grouping very likely. When you get to about 22 or 23, head over to the giants. This is where you will being to have diffiiculty finding a group. They simply do not appreciate the power and low agro of a rain spell. learn to root park. Enchanters are near usless here becuase you can't mezz or stun a giant. When you hit about 25 or 26, make a B-Line to the Crypt of Dalnir and dont leave till you hit 32, maybe even break out of 35. From here, go to the ToFS and stay put a while. <br>
<br>
Now, before everyone burns me for this, let me say a few things:<br>
1) Notice there are a lot of places where the damage-output-of-MOB and HP-of-MOB are not too bad (except giants.) In fact, these are the places where you can root and nuke solo when you cant find a group.<br>
2) Learn to group early, because if you are bad at grouping it will agravate the grouping issues later.<br>
3) Soloing at low levels is a waste. You need frineds BEFORE you get int your 20s and 30s. Find a guild, and they may have better advice for you.<br>
4) Make friends with every enchanter and cleric you can, they are your ticket into a group. Every enchanter and cleric I have worked with learns VERY quickly that I can make AGRO faster than any melee can, and unlike most melees, I watch the whole fight, not just the mod I'm autoattacking/kicking/bashing.<br>
<br>
Ohh one more thing, loot and items done mean hell squat to a caster they way they do a melee class. that extra 10 int will give you enough mana to cast root twice or maybe a small nuke. That will save you arse in a fight once every other blue moon. forget buying items early on, just go out and make coin for spells and save up for the really useful items. <br>
<br>
well there is my 2CP <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
